Done. Bringr-93j.26 is complete and closed.

**What changed** — `Bringr/PreferencesView.swift`:
- The Preferences root was a `VStack` pinned to a fixed `height: 720` that had grown each time a section was added (560 → 620 → 720) and was cramped. Wrapped the sections in a `ScrollView` and fixed the window at `460 × 600`, so content scrolls instead of the window stretching taller as settings accumulate.
- DRY'd the five repeated `Text(title).font(.title2).bold()` + content + `Divider()` blocks into a `section(_:isFirst:content:)` helper that handles the dividers — a new setting is now a single `section("X") { xSection }` line.
- Removed the now-pointless trailing `Spacer`. No `BringrApp.swift` change — `.windowResizability(.contentSize)` sizes the window to the ScrollView's fixed frame.

**Quality gates** — build SUCCEEDED, `swiftlint lint --strict` 0 violations, all 206 tests pass. App relaunched and left running (PID 33344) for your use; no crash.

